------------------------------------------------------------------------------
REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To install mokarra, you will need the following minimum requirements:
  * Linux - tested on AMD64
  * FreePascal Compiler >= 2.6.4 (fpc) including RTL & FCL units
  * Rake >= 10.0 - (requires ruby, >=1.9)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BUILD
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALL
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Currently, Mokarra is a static binary. Copy the resulting file 'mokarra' to
a directory within your path.  A configuration file is not shipped with the
distribution, but the mokarra tool will help you create one.

 #  mokarra -c 

You will need filesystem permission to create /etc/mokarra.cfg

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USING REEF
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To use REEF, you will need an existing snapshot of a perbuilt REEF directory
layout, or you will need to create one from scratch.  See the REEF document
for more information.
